laboratory_examinations.findings: Markedly inflamed and thickened appendix measuring up to 10 mm, extensive stranding with small amount of fluid surrounding the appendix, tiny locule of intraperitoneal gas adjacent to the ascending colon likely representing ex peritoneal air secondary to perforation.
MIXED BACTERIAL FLORA (>= 3 COLONY TYPES), CONSISTENT WITH SKIN AND/OR GENITAL CONTAMINATION. Result was 201.0 K/uL, which is within the referenced range of 150.0 to 400.0 K/uL.
